          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The cyclotron arc was modulated to produce",
                "bursts of fast neutrons at the target. The neutrons",
                "were then slowed down in a hydrogenous \"source\" and",
                "pass down a paraffin and boron-carbide collimator to",
                "the detector which has the form of an ionization",
                "chamber. The pulses from the detector were passed to",
                "an amplifier which was modulated so that the  time",
                "distribution of the pulses occurring in the",
                "ionization chamber can be observed. Since the",
                "measured time of flight for a neutron to pass from",
                "the source to the detector was a function of the",
                "energy, the time distribution of pulses in the",
                "ionization chamber was a function of the sensitivity",
                "of the detector for neutrons of various energies and",
                "of the energy distribution of the neutron beam. By",
                "comparing number of 235U counts in the chamber to",
                "that of a BF3 detector the energy sensitivity was",
                "determined for the ionization chamber."
              ]
            }
          ],
